# Root Files Sync

When you add or change code under `App/`, update root project files if needed.

## requirements.txt

- Add any new third-party dependency with a sensible version constraint
- Remove packages no longer imported anywhere in `App/`

## .gitignore

- Add patterns for new generated artifacts, caches, local env files, or build outputs introduced by the change

## README.md

- Document new features, CLI commands, API endpoints, or setup steps when behavior or usage changes
- Keep the project description accurate as scope evolves

## When to skip

- Pure refactors with no new deps, artifacts, or user-facing behavior — no root file updates required
